In the [C4 model](https://c4model.com/), the four C's represent [context](https://c4model.com/#SystemContextDiagram), [containers](https://c4model.com/#ContainerDiagram), [components](https://c4model.com/#ComponentDiagram), and [code](https://c4model.com/#CodeDiagram). These different levels help tell the right story, to the right audience.

## Level 1 - Data Platform system context

This is the highest level of abstraction and provides an overview of the entire system. It shows the system under consideration and its external dependencies, such as users, external systems, and APIs. The intended audience is everybody, both technical and non-technical people, inside and outside of the engineering team.

When thinking about the system context we can ask ourselves the following questions.

- What is the scope of the system we're building? What are we looking after as a team?
- Who is using it and what are they doing?
- What system integrations does it need to support?
  
